Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.67,0:00:09.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,The countless flowers,\Nenveloped in light...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.74,0:00:19.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,...gaze at tomorrow\Nwith unwavering eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.36,0:00:39.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone wishes for me to be pure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.50,0:00:46.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but what can I bring\Nwith me to the frayed skies?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.71,0:00:53.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,What I've made my own\Nby breaking off flowers in bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.09,0:00:59.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,All such sinful things...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.49,0:01:06.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why did I stop making\Npromises with the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.97,0:01:14.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because even if I try\Nto run far from all the pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.21,0:01:20.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,...a cold wind rustles\Nmy hair... Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:28.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Where can I ever find the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.36,0:01:34.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am Anubituf,\Nthe captain of the Arcus Prima...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.73,0:01:39.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,...one of the largest airships\Nin Simulacrum Kyuukoku's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.73,0:01:45.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Three air squadrons, Simoun chors,\Nare stationed on the Arcus Prima.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.64,0:01:50.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest,\NChor Caput, and Chor Rubor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.51,0:01:56.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,But Chor Tempest, once prided for\Ndefense and flawless Ri Majons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.35,0:02:01.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,...has lost its high standing and is now\Nbeing relegated to reserve status.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.69,0:02:06.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,And now, as we escort\Nthe Plumbum highland delegation...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.69,0:02:10.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,...to international waters, where\Na peace conference is scheduled...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.03,0:02:16.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,...tensions in Chor Tempest over its\Nnew members have sparked a brawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.54,0:02:23.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest has been ordered to\Ndisband as soon as we return to port.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:29.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,For those with reasons for wanting\Nto continue flying the Simouns...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:30.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,...it is a bitter sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.05,0:02:34.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Either way, when it's time\Nto journey to the Spring...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.45,0:02:36.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,...one can no longer fly a Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.96,0:02:41.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,And now the peace\Nconference is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:49.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.37,0:02:54.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,We understand that your priestesses\Nare all fluent in Kyuukoku's language.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.04,0:02:59.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,But for translating purposes,\Nwouldn't just one suffice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.18,0:03:05.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,We are not mere interpreters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:08.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,We also watch over\Nthis important conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:11.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,And several are needed\Nfor certain ceremonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:13.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:18.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,We should have some of Tempus\NSpatium's priestesses attend as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:20.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:25.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,They are not merely priestesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.04,0:03:27.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but soldiers too, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.58,0:03:39.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,How long will you snivel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:42.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, we've been disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:44.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,We should be crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.66,0:03:49.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,But at least now we can\Nfinally stop flying Simouns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:57.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina, what have\Nyou been doing since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:04:01.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,You lived with your mother after\Nyour father passed away, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.07,0:04:03.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.68,0:04:09.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've got to keep flying Simouns.\NI have to remain a sibylla...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:14.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's just like Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.59,0:04:19.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,You want to go on\Nbeing a sibylla too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.89,0:04:20.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:25.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why? As long as you're a sibylla,\Nyou don't have to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.23,0:04:26.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.03,0:04:30.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,We all want to go to the Spring,\Nbut since becoming sibyllae...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:35.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,...we have to take part in this war now\Nand are unable to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.11,0:04:39.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's not like it's forbidden.\NJust quit being a sibylla, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.71,0:04:42.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,After being finally\Nchosen after such toil?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:47.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,I do have my pride as a priestess.\NAvoiding the front line isn't an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.62,0:04:49.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,We all have our reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.55,0:04:54.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but I've never seen anyone who\Nwanted to avoid going to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.49,0:04:57.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh? If you want to see, be my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.30,0:04:58.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:01.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:04.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:09.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,This ballroom is where Chor Tempest\Nsocializes. It's always been that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:12.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,People like the captain\Nnever decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:15.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,But it's always been\Nthat way, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:18.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,You guys never used to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:22.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're on standby and might\Nscramble at any time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:23.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.00,0:05:39.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, jeez, I can't stand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:43.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big Sister, why don't\Nyou come to my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:47.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, everybody! Big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.85,0:05:49.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big news! Big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.42,0:05:54.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,She always seems to be having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.42,0:05:58.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's been decided that just two\Nof the highland priestesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:06:01.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,...will be allowed\Nto attend the peace conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:07.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Meaning that this priestess here,\NAnglas, will not be allowed to attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.60,0:06:11.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,She'll stay with Chor Tempest\Nuntil the conference is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:14.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because we're fellow priestesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.17,0:06:18.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,We can leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.34,0:06:22.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'll be patrolling the conference site.\NI hope everything's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:25.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't offend our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.19,0:06:32.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,The only thing is we don't\Nspeak the same language...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.43,0:06:37.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am not fluent, but I can speak a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:46.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've heard many highland priestesses\Nare from the border near Kyuukoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.40,0:06:51.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right, speaking of which, that area's\Ntribes travel between the countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:57.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,They say our god was once\Nthe same deity that you worship here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:07:00.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's why, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.32,0:07:03.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,You feel an affinity with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:10.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,The little one is Rimone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.56,0:07:14.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,The two on the right are Alty and Kaim.\NThey're sisters, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:15.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.93,0:07:19.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rimone, Alty, Kaim, Morinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.07,0:07:22.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,And there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:26.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Starting from the right, Paraietta,\NDominüra, and Roatreamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.54,0:07:30.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta, Dominüra, Roatreamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:33.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,What a lovely name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.65,0:07:36.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's a very noble name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.12,0:07:41.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,From a venerable family that's borne\Ngenerations of Simoun sibyllae.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.73,0:07:45.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,And the girl who just spoke up\Nis Mamina. Next to her is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.50,0:07:46.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm Yun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.83,0:07:51.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I wish for\Na speedy end to the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:55.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to know there will soon\Nbe peace between our countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.67,0:07:57.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina and Yun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:01.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's what I wish for too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.21,0:08:02.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,My name's Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:04.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.35,0:08:06.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let's see... Who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.85,0:08:09.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,The girl in the very back is Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:13.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,The only one missing is Neviril.\NAnd that's everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:19.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:22.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Now that introductions are done...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:24.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.54,0:08:32.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're the only one\Nshe didn't call by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.51,0:08:35.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she said\Neveryone's name but mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.88,0:08:38.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Does she have\Nto say every single name?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.65,0:08:39.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,How tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.08,0:08:42.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,I know it is, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:45.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Say, what do you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:47.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,We're priestesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.66,0:08:51.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,But we turned the Simouns\Ninto weapons of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.43,0:08:53.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,To do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:57.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,In the eyes of normal priestesses\Nlike you, it's peculiar, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:03.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is very cold in the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.84,0:09:08.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,We're blessed by\Na compassionate god, but even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:12.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Every year, there is a cold snap,\Nresulting in many deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:09:14.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am a priestess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:20.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,...so I pray that those who have\Nperished may find bliss in God's arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.96,0:09:23.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.76,0:09:26.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,When we first started as sibyllae...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.50,0:09:31.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I thought we would fly Simouns\Nin divine ceremonies like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.67,0:09:36.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're right. We should be flying\Nthe Simouns in order to pray...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:38.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,What a carefree attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.31,0:09:44.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,You take becoming a sibylla\Nfor granted, so you can say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.88,0:09:47.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that, Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:54.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for this war,\NI never could have become a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.46,0:10:03.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,There were only a handful\Nof young girls in my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:07.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't hard to serve the great\Ntemple as a priestess in training.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:09.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.45,0:10:16.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:21.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,When I become a sibylla,\Nwill you fly with me as my pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:24.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,You? A sibylla?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.19,0:10:29.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibyllae are selected by Tempus\NSpatium. People of humble birth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.43,0:10:35.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,And then that day came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.67,0:10:39.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Plumbum highland's death squad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.94,0:10:43.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,...crossed the border and\Ntook up position in our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:49.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Their goal was of course to steal\Nthe Simouns from the great temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.01,0:10:51.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,There was no time to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.05,0:10:56.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,We had to launch the Simouns\Nand repulse them from the skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:11:01.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,The sibyllae said, "We are\Npriestesses. We can't go into battle."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:06.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,The dux turned to\Nthe trainees for volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.27,0:11:11.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.20,0:11:15.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tempus Spatium will never allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:18.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,One such as you\Ncould never fly a Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.55,0:11:56.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,And so I became a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:12:00.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,But only because I was\Naccomplished in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.92,0:12:04.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, being of low birth\Nand having no connections...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.26,0:12:07.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I would've been stripped\Nof my post right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.26,0:12:11.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,If only I could pair up\Nwith Neviril... With Sibylla Aurea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.96,0:12:15.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then no one could ever\Ntreat me like an upstart again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:20.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I could prove there's\Nno better sibylla in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:22.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,But now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:24.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:26.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.05,0:12:30.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's not something one\Nshould tell another land's priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.88,0:12:32.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:35.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,But anyway, I'm sure keeping\Nme company is very dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:38.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please go about your day freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.49,0:12:43.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh? You can take a tour of the ship\Nas long as it's not a restricted area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:45.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'd like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.40,0:12:48.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then as my guide... Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.10,0:12:53.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's Aer, all right? Call me by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:43.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is it all right to go into\Nanother god's chapel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.15,0:13:46.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned earlier,\Nthe recent theory is that our god...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.09,0:13:53.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,...was once the same as your\Nown deity, Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:58.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then does that mean your country\Nused to be a colony of ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.84,0:14:00.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.71,0:14:02.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Before Tempus Spatium...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.81,0:14:06.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,...there may have been\Nan even more ancient religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.55,0:14:14.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:16.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm not a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.22,0:14:19.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.19,0:14:23.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, forget her. She's just here since\Nshe doesn't want to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.03,0:14:25.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,Praying to gods is trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.03,0:14:30.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? You haven't\Npicked a gender yet either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, no, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.57,0:14:41.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you're not sure, forcing an answer\Nwould be even more ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.13,0:14:59.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,A Plumbum dictionary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.36,0:15:00.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's the problem?\NYou and I are a pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.60,0:15:04.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.72,0:15:21.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.39,0:15:23.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'll check on the conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.22,0:15:24.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.56,0:15:28.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do you think...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.10,0:15:41.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Those fireworks were a signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:43.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,First, where's the priestess?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.88,0:15:46.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer-sama, Sibylla Aurea is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:07.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's got my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:09.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why would she...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:15.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:18.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's as it seems.\NThis is how they do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:20.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,The conference was\Na diversion for their infiltration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.08,0:16:22.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,To take a Simoun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.98,0:16:25.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,You can't fly that Simoun, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.15,0:16:30.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's a priestess, right? If there\Nwere two, it might be possible to fly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:35.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,If she does, what are those people\Nin the conference planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.13,0:16:38.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Waporif, block the maintenance\Nhangar off from the conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.00,0:16:41.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't let two highland\Npriestesses rendezvous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.53,0:16:45.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear her? Move it!\NWe're blocking all access!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:50.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Do you really think\Nyou're going to pull this off?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:52.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.68,0:17:00.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Big Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.85,0:17:02.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Alty! Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.35,0:17:05.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,Grab her!\NDon't let her touch that Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.64,0:17:20.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.34,0:17:21.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:34.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you're unsure of yourself,\Nyou'll never find an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:36.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,Run, Floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:37.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:39.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!\NRight. Bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.22,0:17:40.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,Run, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:42.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,She's got bombs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:47.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:20.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:27.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:42.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,Nearly all the Simouns\Nhere were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.22,0:18:44.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have to see\Nif the ones spared work...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.62,0:18:45.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Which can fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.99,0:18:48.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Only the Simouns on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:52.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Only Chor Tempest's\NSimouns, you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.37,0:18:58.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Aer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:01.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,That girl called out "Aer"...\NAt the very end...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:03.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.54,0:19:06.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,But why? Why my name...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.84,0:19:09.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because it's not\Na person's name to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:13.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,The word "aer" in her own language...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:16.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,...means "the highest love of all."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.02,0:19:22.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,"Aer" means "the love of god"\Nin the Plumbum language.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.53,0:19:28.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.80,0:19:33.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just what is it about this "love of god"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:38.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can it make\Nsomeone do a thing like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.85,0:20:24.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea,\Nplease fly with me as your pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.62,0:20:28.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just heard that Chor Tempest's\NSimouns are the only ones intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.69,0:20:31.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're completely sure\Nabout this, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.80,0:20:34.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,We don't have time not to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer, what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.14,0:20:42.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.67,0:20:45.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:55.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer, you came here\Nto fly a Simoun, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.09,0:20:59.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just don't want to go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.63,0:21:03.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,But is that a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:09.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't even have\Nlove of god or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.47,0:21:13.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,You needn't come up with an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:30.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm unsure too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:33.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,About being a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.26,0:21:35.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,About going into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.39,0:21:39.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Whether those are\Nthe right things to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:43.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,You and I are completely\Ndifferent in every respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:47.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,But we're alike in just one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.44,0:21:50.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Stand up, Aer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.77,0:21:52.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am your pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:10.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,One second is enough. Right the ship.\NWe're launching the Simouns.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.00,0:22:13.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,Rubor and Caput were destroyed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.20,0:22:15.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest will be going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.09,0:22:47.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is played by my wounds...\Nthe song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.83,0:22:51.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let it ring out over\Nthe grieving universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.07,0:22:59.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Can we change tomorrow?\NDon't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.11,0:23:06.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to let you know\Nhow my heart's overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.53,0:23:19.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,"I want to get closer to you."\N"I want to feel your pulse."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.63,0:23:24.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was too defiant,\Nand I took the long way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.80,0:23:28.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,The blue moon is swaying silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.81,0:23:32.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,My true heart's desire is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:38.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can't reach you.\NMy tears of pain trickle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.68,0:23:44.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Soar away into the sky, song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.22,0:23:47.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Carrying my love that came too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.66,0:23:53.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,What can I do to change tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.33,0:23:59.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just hold on to "now" the way it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.01,0:24:06.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:06.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,To Be Continued\NWe will soon be performing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.51,0:24:08.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,We will soon be performing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.58,0:24:13.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,...our last Ri Majon as members of\NChor Tempest at the great temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:15.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time on Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.35,0:24:17.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Hearing\NNext time on Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.55,0:24:19.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Hearing\NThe Hearing.
